fondant help is this fondant good for cakes http www cooks com rec doc html no stop nuts in fondant plain sugar please compare rolled fondant ingredients tablespoon plus teaspoons unflavored gelatin cup cold water cup glucose tablespoons solid vegetable shortening tablespoon glycerin cups sifted confectioner's sugar about lbs icing color and flavoring as desired prep combine gelatin and cold water let stand until thick place gelatin mixture in top of double boiler and heat until dissolved add glucose mix well stir in shortening and just before completely melted remove from heat add glycerin flavoring and color cool until lukewarm next place cups confectioner's sugar in a bowl and make a well pour the lukewarm gelatin mixture into the well and stir with a wooden spoon mixing in sugar and adding more a little at a time until stickiness disappears knead in remaining sugar knead until the fondant is smooth pliable and does not stick to your hands if fondant is too soft add more sugar if too stiff add water a drop at a time use fondant immediately or store in airtight container in a cool dry place do not refrigerate or freeze when ready to use knead again until soft this recipe makes approx oz enough to cover a x in high cake Tofu Brewery Coffee Halva Cooking weights and measures Japanese cuisine Tea Chocolate Chili con carne Mayonnaise Glycerin Turkish coffee Honey Cuisine of Denmark Soap bubble Beer Cheese Turkish Delight Sushi Idli Food preservation Cookie Puff pastry Rum Pottery Pizza Casting Cuisine of the Philippines Wine making Vinegar Ketchup Gelatin Cantonese cuisine Cake Jewish cuisine Sugar beet Bulk vending Cookware and bakeware Soap Soup Ramen Tortilla Bong Sugarcane Confectionery Sauerkraut Butter Dairy Sake Pancake Glass Starch Stir frying Soft drink Chewing gum Plastic In-N-Out Burger Kosher foods Barbecue Milkshake Ice Gumbo Rice pudding Ammonia Seitan Korean cuisine Hamster Cuisine of Malaysia Gilding Sucrose Cuisine of Laos Chocolate Salty Balls Wine C